1. using jenkins docs: https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/linux/ install jenkins
2. install firefox if not already installed
3. open jenkins using localhost:8080, install suggested plugins 
4. create a job called "first_job" with three steps
	1. echo "First step"
        2. echo "second step"
        3. echo "third step"


1. Create a credentials in jenkins with your email and password of dockerhub (manage jenkins => credentials)
2. install docker pipeline plugin ( manage jenkins => plugins )
3. on your server run ( sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins, sudo systemctl restart jenkins)
4. create a job called secondjob, select it's type to be pipeline
5. select Helloworld pipeline, edit the pipeline to add script directiv einside the steps
6. build and push to dockerhub => to get docker url "cat ~/.docker/config.json"
